      "writtenOn": "2019-09-20T19:45:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ll add a case for \"UNKNOWN\". The default case is a NOTREACHED() /if/ we assume that the GTest results format will not change its current statuses. If we /don\u0027t/ assume that, and treat unrecognized GTest status as fatal for test conversion, we\u0027ll lose the rest of the test data. To avoid that, WDYT about logging the error at the test conversion level, but still setting STATUS_UNSPECIFIED?\n\n(Reordered the cases to match where they\u0027re defined in https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/base/test/launcher/test_result.h?l\u003d50\u0026rcl\u003d0cc5b6a1a34d9124256a4eb7199e9c2daa8b21ba rather than where they\u0027re converted in https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/base/test/launcher/test_result.cc?l\u003d63\u0026rcl\u003d0cc5b6a1a34d9124256a4eb7199e9c2daa8b21ba",
